Trees will be teaching Animal Science Pathway courses, as well as Principles of Ag. She comes to us from West Texas A&M University in Canyon, TX where she received both her Bachelors and Masters in Agriculture fields. post_text: Hello! This year due to us not returning to school Yorktown FFA Officer Tryouts will be online this year. We are still working out the fine details so please be patient with us. The first step is joining our FFA Officer Tryouts classroom. The google code can be found on the little flyer attached. You will need to join by Friday April 24th, 2020 at Midnight. This will give us a head count of students running. All information regarding tryouts will be in this classroom. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to reach out to Mrs. Vandenberg or Mr. Gowens. have a great rest of your weekend.

post_text: We had our LDE teams compete this last Friday in Schulenburg. Our Sr Skills Team made up of Andrew Yeretsky, Lupe Mcguinis, Dylan Yoeman and Devin Leister placed sixth in competition. Public Relations- Brooklyn Corpus, Lacie Rios, Drew Alexander, Aubrie Ruppert placed 4th and Senior Creed Speaking- Katy Gwosdz placed 2nd. Katy advanced to Area which will be November 17th in Brenham. Congrats to all for their hard work and dedication and good luck to Katy on her advancement.

post_text: Western Days has come to an end and the Yorkotwn FFA members were very busy this week. We kicked off the weekend by participating in the parade. The students worked hard all week getting the float ready. Right after the parade some of our FFA members volunteered their time working the Hay Dive Saturday and Sunday. These students earned lots of community service for their record books. We‚Äôd like to thank the the city of Yorktown and the Western Days committee for giving us the chance to give back to the community.

post_text: Attention FFA Moms and Dads, Grandparents, and Neighbors!!! The Yorktown FFA will be begin their annual fundraiser of fruit, meat, and cookie dough. The students will be getting their take home packets today, and will have them till the turn in date which is October 11th. This will ensure the delivery of your products by Thanksgiving! This year we will be using Seitz Fundraising company. They have just launched a new app that now allows you to use your credit or debit card. Fruit will be on the order form however, it will not be delivered until December when the fruit is picked off the trees. Please find your favorite FFA student and support them in this fundraiser. Please share this post to get the news out!!

post_text: Friday, the FFA's Wildlife Classes had a great day in Karnes City for the Lonsome Dove Fest School Day Sessions. post_text: It‚Äôs that time again! Yorktown‚Äôs 1st FFA meeting will be held in the Ag building Monday, September 10th. There will be a meal provided for all FFA members and their families starting at 7:00pm. So come hungry! The meeting will start at 7:30pm. Followed after the meeting there will be a MANDATORY Yorktown FFA stock show meeting. If you plan to show an animal or Ag mechanics project you and parent must attend. We will be going over the new changes, rules, and plans for this year. There is a sign up sheet in the AG building. Please sign up so that we know how many guests you are bringing! Come out and have fun with us!

post_text: Today has been a a busy day for the Yorktown FFA chapter. This morning we were up bright and early for the first ever Area XI business caucus meeting. Katie Hughes and Katy Gwosdz represented Yorktown as our voting delegates. They got to vote on changes to the bylaws that will be used this upcoming school year! These students were apart of history today.
